				<li id="16524164" class="cmnt-root" data="33" data-d="1647511206000"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment-box"><div class="avatar"><img src="/images/avatar.png" alt="" /><div class="comment-username">Anonymous</div></div><div class="comment"><div class="title"><span class="txt-subject"></span><input style="display: none;" class="txt-subject-ed"><span class="right cmt-ui"><a href="https://fextralife.com/forums/t578510/Black-Flame" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">17 Mar 2022 06:00</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a class="report-post" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/report.php?f=193&p=16524164" rel="nofollow" target="_blank" title="report this post"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flag" aria-hidden="true"></span></a></span></div><p class="txt-comment">The damage-over-time from Black Flame is static at 5% of max health over about 2 seconds. Tested on the fire slugs outside of Guest Hall in Volcano Manor with 40, 20, and 99 FTH: in each case it did exactly 21 damage (they&apos;re immune to normal fire damage but not the DoT). Also not affected by any talismans, incant scaling, or seal type. This makes it a good pick for builds where faith isn&apos;t your primary stat.<br/><br/>The normal fire damage increases with incant scaling, can be boosted by Fire Scorpion Talisman, etc. </p><textarea style="display: none;" class="txt-comment-ed"></textarea><div class="clearfix"><a role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#zz-16524164" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Reply</a><a id="btnExpandComment" role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#replies-16524164" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Replies (<span class="replies">2</span>)</a><div class="vote pull-right"><section class="t-up"><span></span><p>35</p><i class="add">+1</i></section><section class="t-down"><span></span><p>2</p><i class="sub">-1</i></section></div></div><div class="collapse-com transparent"><div class="co