				<li id="16477469" class="cmnt-root" data="7" data-d="1646792021000"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment-box"><div class="avatar"><img src="/images/avatar.png" alt="" /><div class="comment-username">Anonymous</div></div><div class="comment"><div class="title"><span class="txt-subject"></span><input style="display: none;" class="txt-subject-ed"><span class="right cmt-ui"><a href="https://fextralife.com/forums/t578510/Black-Flame" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">08 Mar 2022 21:13</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a class="report-post" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/report.php?f=193&p=16477469" rel="nofollow" target="_blank" title="report this post"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flag" aria-hidden="true"></span></a></span></div><p class="txt-comment">After some testing on &quot;Banished Knight&quot;, It seems that &quot;Black Flame&quot; gains a &quot;backstab bonus&quot; meaning damage increases if you strike the backs of enemies. With 41 Faith and &quot;Godslayer Seal +11&quot;, starting combat with a fully charged &quot;Black Flame&quot;, did 434 (Initial + [DOT]) to the back of a full hp knight, The second &quot;Black Flame&quot; ball did 350 (Initial + [DOT]), to his front-side, leaving him on 1 hp. 434 + 351 = 785 HP. The incantation also interacts with &quot;Flame, Grant me Strength&quot;, an incantation that boosts fire damage among other things. It&apos;s unclear weather the [DOT] counts as fire or physical damage, but I assume only the initial impact of &quot;Black Flame&quot; does fire damage, while the [DOT] does physical. With the buff, The first fireball did 517 (initial + [DOT]) to his back (front-side damage is 416), and the second fireball did 395, killing the knight instantly (NO [DOT]).</p><textarea style="display: none;" class="txt-comment-ed"></textarea><div class="clearfix"><a role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#zz-16477469" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Reply</a><a id="btnExpandComment"